{
  "info": {
    "name": "Multi-Tenant CRM (Phases 0-4)",
    "_postman_id": "b1a2c3d4-0004-4a00-8000-crm0000004",
    "description": "API collection for the multi-tenant SaaS CRM, covering Phases 0-4: tenancy, JWT auth, RBAC, members, leads, pipeline/stages, deals, tasks, and the audit/activity feed.\n\n## How tenancy works\nThe API selects the tenant from the request **subdomain** (e.g. `acme.crm.local`). This collection sends that subdomain as a `Host` header automatically (see the collection Pre-request Script), so it works against `http://localhost:8000` **without** editing your hosts file.\n\n## Setup\n1. Start the stack: `docker compose up -d` and seed: `docker compose run --rm web python manage.py seed_tenants`.\n2. Pick a tenant by setting the `tenant` variable (`acme` or `globex`).\n3. Run **Auth > Login** first — it stores `access_token` / `refresh_token` for every other request.\n\n## Demo users (password `password123`)\n`owner@acme.crm.local`, `admin@acme.crm.local`, `manager@acme.crm.local`, `sales_rep@acme.crm.local`, `viewer@acme.crm.local` (and the same for `globex`).\n\n## RBAC quick reference\n- read = any member  - create/update = Sales Rep+  - delete = Manager+  - manage members / create stages = Manager/Admin+",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}", "type": "string" }]
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Route the request to the right tenant by sending the subdomain as Host.",
          "var tenant = pm.variables.get('tenant') || 'acme';",
          "pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'Host', value: tenant + '.crm.local' });"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8000" },
    { "key": "tenant", "value": "acme" },
    { "key": "email", "value": "owner@acme.crm.local" },
    { "key": "password", "value": "password123" },
    { "key": "access_token", "value": "" },
    { "key": "refresh_token", "value": "" },
    { "key": "lead_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "stage_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "won_stage_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "deal_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "task_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "member_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "tag_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "note_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "customfield_id", "value": "" },
    { "key": "savedview_id", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register (new workspace)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register/", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "auth", "register", ""] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"tenant_name\": \"New Co\",\n  \"slug\": \"newco\",\n  \"email\": \"founder@newco.crm.local\",\n  \"password\": \"password123\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Public onboarding: creates a new tenant + Owner user + `<slug>.crm.local` subdomain. To use the new workspace, set `tenant` = the slug and log in.\n\n**Phase 5:** queues a welcome email to the new Owner (async). Watch it run with `docker compose logs -f celery-worker`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.code === 200);",
                  "var j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', j.access);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', j.refresh);",
                  "pm.test('got tokens', () => !!j.access && !!j.refresh);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login/", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "auth", "login", ""] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}" },
            "description": "Authenticate against the current `tenant` subdomain. Stores `access_token` + `refresh_token`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.code === 200);",
                  "var j = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (j.access) pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', j.access);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh/", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "auth", "refresh", ""] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"refresh\": \"{{refresh_token}}\"\n}" }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Me",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me/", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "auth", "me", ""] },
            "description": "Current user, role, and tenant."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Tenant info",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/tenant/", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "tenant", ""] },
            "description": "Resolve the tenant from the subdomain (404 for unknown subdomains)."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
